HEADWORD: Scholasticism
<hw>Scho*las"ti*cism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The method or
subtleties of the schools of philosophy; scholastic formality;
scholastic doctrines or philosophy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The spirit of the old <qex>scholasticism</qex> . . . spurned
laborious investigation and slow induction.</q> <rj><qau>J. P.
Smith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scholia</ent>⟦br⟧
